size:
Oris Ocean Trilogy Set - a limited & numbered edition set of only 200 sets, with all 3 pieces sharing the same limited edition number. The trio of watches includes the: • Oris Blue Whale limited edition 200 pieces, available exclusively as part of the Oris Ocean Trilogy set).

• Oris Great Barrier Reef III limited edition 2000 pieces.

• Oris Clean Ocean limited edition 2000 pieces.

The set is delivered in an exclusive & eye-catching presentation box produced from used plastic bottles. Only chemically inert recycled plastic waste was selected as part of the process. The box is created in 4 steps: • Use plastic bottles are collected.

• The plastic bottles are then shredded into small pieces.

• The pieces are selectively hand arranged & then pressed into a panel. The hand selection & positioning of the various colored bottle makes each panel unique.

• Finally the panels are cut to size & assembled as the outer shell of the Oris Ocean Trilogy presentation box .

Oris Blue Whale 01 743 7734 4185-Set: • Case diameter: 45.50mm

• Case back: Special engraving with Blue Whale image.

• Crown: screw down.

• Bezel: Blue ceramic with diving scale.

• Dial: Gradient blue dial, applied hour markers with luminous fill, hands with luminous fill.

• Water resistance: 500m.

• Features: Chronograph function, small seconds sub-dial at 9 o'clock, date window at 4.30 o'clock.

• Movement: Oris caliber 771 (base SW 510), beats at 28,800 vph, contains 27 jewels & has a power reserve of +/- 48 hours.

• Case back: Special engraving with Blue Whale image.

• Crown: screw down.

• Bezel: Blue ceramic with diving scale.

• Water resistance: 300m.

• Features: Central date indicator hand.

• Movement: Oris caliber 743 (base SW 220-1), beats at 28,800 vph, contains 28 jewels & has a power reserve of +/- 38 hours.

Oris Clean Ocean 01 733 7732 4185-Set: • Case diameter: 39.50mm

• Case back: Special engraving with medallion made of recycled PET plastics set into the case back.

• Crown: screw down.

• Dial: Gradient blue dial, applied hour markers with luminous fill, hands with luminous fill.

• Water resistance: 300m.

• Features: Date window at 6 o'clock.

ABOUT


This pre-owned, Omega Speedmaster Date 323.21.40.40.02.001 is in like new condition. The watch comes as a full set (undated warranty card), along with 1 year warranty from The Watch Village.




All of our watches undergo a thorough inspection of accuracy, functionality and condition to meet our strict standards. Additionally, we check each watch against records to ensure authenticity and ownership status.




This rare Speedmaster features a striking silver dial that is decorated with gold accents from the hands, numeral markers and complication outlines. A contrasting 18K yellow gold tachymetre bezel sits upon a 40mm stainless steel casebody, which is attached to a matching stainless-steel bracelet. All powered by the Omega Calibre 1164 automatic movement.

NEW Speedmaster Professional Moonwatch Rose Gold 310.60.42.50.01.001
size:
Brand new, Factory Sealed, Complete Set, December 2021




The Speedmaster Moonwatch is one of the world’s most iconic timepieces. Having been a part of all six moon landings, the legendary chronograph is an impressive representation of the brand’s adventurous pioneering spirit.




Presented on a five-arched-links-per-row bracelet, this 42 mm Moonwatch in 18K Sedna gold features sapphire crystal glass on the front as well as on the caseback. Inspired by the 4th generation Speedmaster style worn on the moon, it also includes an asymmetrical case, black step dial and the famous dot over 90 on the anodised aluminium bezel ring.




The watch is driven by the OMEGA Co-Axial Master Chronometer Calibre 3861, which powers the small seconds sub-dial, 30-minute recorder and 12-hour recorder, along with the central chronograph function.




Anti-magnetic




The movement is unaffected by exposure to strong magnetic fields, even those greater than 1.5 tesla (15,000 gauss).


Chronograph




The chronograph function is a mechanism for measuring time intervals. A chronograph watch can therefore be used to time events while displaying the time like any traditional watch.


Chronometer




Label given to a watch which has undergone precision tests and received a certificate from an official body (COSC).


Master Chronometer Certified




Guaranteeing the Swiss industry’s highest standard of precision, performance and magnetic-resistance, as set by the Swiss Federal Institute of Metrology (METAS).


Sedna Gold




Sedna Gold is an 18K rose gold alloy, fusing pure gold with copper and palladium, in order to guarantee that your gold watch has long lasting lustre.


Small seconds




A hand on a sub-dial which tracks seconds typically it completes a full rotation in one minute.


Tachymeter




A tachymeter watch has a function for measuring speed. It is a chronograph with a graduated dial on which speed can be read in kilometres per hour based on a 1000 metre distance.


Transparent case back




A transparent case back - frequently made of sapphire - makes it possible to see the movement inside the watch.
